main event: Multiple unidentified flying objects were observed near the Sioux Army Depot in Nebraska in 1965.
interesting points: Two objects, white in color and the size of the North Star, were observed moving rapidly at about 20 degrees per second through binoculars.
Three objects, the size of a dollar coin with a blinking light in the center, were observed moving at a rate of about 600 mph towards Cheyenne.
Two objects were observed drifting southwest over the Sioux Army Depot, and later two more objects were observed moving westward and disappearing in the distance.
Three objects appeared in the middle of the Big Dipper constellation, moved on a level course, and then threw out white objects as they approached the Pleiades.
The objects were observed by a variety of military personnel, including a security guard, staff sergeant, and members of a Geodetic Survey Team.
sighted object: multiple unidentified flying objects of various sizes, shapes, and behaviors
